## Schema Files (defaults/schemas/)

Named `*.schema.json`. Define object types and validation rules.

```json
{
  "name": "add_npc",
  "description": "Add a new NPC to the knowledge graph",
  "properties": {
    "name": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "NPC name",
      "required": true,
      "validation": { "min_length": 1, "max_length": 100 }
    },
    "role": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "NPC role",
      "required": true,
      "validation": { "allowed_values": ["merchant", "guard", "noble"] }
    },
    "currentLocation": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Current location",
      "relationship": {
        "edgeType": "located_in",
        "targetType": "location"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Property types
`string`, `text`, `number`, `boolean`, `array`, `object`, `reference`

### Validation rules
`min_length`, `max_length`, `min_value`, `max_value`, `pattern` (regex), `allowed_values`, `required`

### Naming convention
Files use `add_` prefix in `name` field (MCP tool convention). `SchemaIngestion` strips the prefix — `add_npc` becomes `npc` internally.

## Import Validation Commands

```bash
# Check JSON syntax
cat file.json | jq .

# Count nodes by type
jq -c 'select(.type == "node") | .nodeType' defaults/data/memory.json | sort | uniq -c

# Find edges
jq -c 'select(.type == "edge")' defaults/data/memory.json | head
```

## Sample Data

`defaults/data/memory.json`: ~220 nodes + ~312 edges from Isaac Asimov's Foundation
universe. Used by the CLI demo and integration tests.

Re-importing this file is safe — deduplication (BUG-6 fix) prevents duplicate nodes.
Cross-session edges resolve correctly via the storage name index (BUG-7 fix).

```bash
# Count nodes by type after import
jq -r 'select(.type == "node") | .nodeType' defaults/data/memory.json | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn

# Verify no parse errors
cargo run --example cli_demo 2>&1 | grep "Parse errors"
```